{{Infobox Aircraft accident |image = Alp doplhinflyer.jpg |caption = A Turkish Airlines Fokker F28 similar to the one involved. |Date = December 23, 1979 |Type = [[Controlled flight into terrain]] |occurrence_type = Accident |Site = Kuyumcuköy, [[Ankara Province|Ankara]], [[Turkey]] |Coordinates = {{Coord|40.32947|N|33.15708|E|type:event|display=inline, title}} |aircraft_type = [[Fokker F28|Fokker F28 Fellowship 1000]] |tail_number = TC-JAT |Ship name = ''Trabzon'' |Operator = [[Turkish Airlines]] |Origin = [[Samsun Airport]], [[Samsun]], Turkey |Destination = [[Esenboğa International Airport]], [[Ankara]], Turkey |Fatalities = 41 |Injuries = 4 |Survivors = 4 |Passengers = 41 |Crew = 4 }}
The '''1979 Turkish Airlines Ankara crash''' occurred on [[December 23]], 1979, when a [[Turkish Airlines]] [[Fokker F28|Fokker F28 Fellowship 1000]] airliner, registration TC-JAT, named ''Trabzon'', on a domestic passenger flight from [[Samsun Airport]] to [[Esenboğa International Airport]] in [[Ankara]], flew into the side of a hill {{convert|1400|m|ft|abbr=on}} near the village of Kuyumcuköy in [[Çubuk]] district of [[Ankara Province]], {{convert|32|km|mi|abbr=on}} north-northeast of the destination airport on approach to landing.<ref name="asn">{{cite web |url=http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19791223-1 |publisher=Aviation Safety Network |title=Aircraft accident Fokker F-28 Fellowship 1000 TC-JAT Ankara-Esenboğa Airport (ESB) |accessdate=2009-09-26 }}</ref>
The crew had deviated from the localizer course while on an [[Instrument Landing System|ILS]] approach experiencing severe turbulence.<ref name="asn" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://airlinehaber.com/bilinmeyenleri-ile-thy-f-28-tc-jap-kazasi/|title=BİLİNMEYENLERİ İLE THY F-28 (TC-JAP) KAZASI - AirlineHaber - Sivil Havacılık Haberleri|date=25 December 2015|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bagimsizhavacilar.com/35-yilin-ardindan-tc-jat-ucagi-kazasi/|title=35 Yılın Ardından TC-JAT Uçağı Kazası|first=Bağımsız|last=Havacılar|date=23 December 2014|publisher=|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref>
==Crew and passengers== The aircraft had four crew and 41 passengers on board. 38 passengers and three crew were killed in the accident.<ref name="asn" />
==Aircraft== The aircraft, a [[Fokker F28 Fellowship]] 1000 with two [[Rolls-Royce Spey|Rolls-Royce RB183-2 "Spey" Mk555-15]] [[turbofan]] [[jet engine]]s, was built by [[Fokker]] with manufacturer serial number 11071, and made its first flight in 1973.<ref name="asn" />
