'''Gharo Wind Power Plant''' is an underconstruction wind power generation project being built in the persistently wind-swept corridor of [[Gharo]], [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]]. This will be one of the first [[wind power]] projects in Pakistan.<ref>http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2006\story_14-5-2006_pg5_10 {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080414060608/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2006 |date=April 14, 2008 }}</ref><ref>http://www.ae-accessenergy.com/news/05-14-2006.pdf</ref> [[Halcrow Group|Halcrow Pakistan]] and the Spanish company, based in Barcelona, Taller d'Enginyeria Ambiental SL have compiled the Enivoronmental Impact Assessment for this project.<ref>http://www.undp.org.pk/images/publications/Environmental%20and%20Socio-Economic%20Baseline%20Report%20of%20Gharo%20Wind%20Carridor.pdf</ref>
The Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) approved $288 million for financing two wind power projects in Sindh in order to overcome power shortage and promote clean energy in [[Pakistan]]. OPIC would help [[Pakistan]] diversify its energy production to include important contributions from renewable energy sources. The OPIC credit facility would help build 50 MW Sapphire wind power plant in [[Gharo-Ketti Bandar wind corridor]], designed to generate 133 giga watt hours of emission-free electricity annually. <ref name="thenews.com.pk">{{cite web|url=http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-4-167078-Two-wind-power-projects-approved|title=The News International: Latest News Breaking, Pakistan News|website=www.thenews.com.pk}}</ref>
Currently, 45 wind power projects of around 3200 MW capacity are under process in [[Pakistan]]. <ref name="thenews.com.pk"/>
