'''''Taken By Storm: The Troubled Science, Policy and Politics of Global Warming''''' is a 2002 book about the [[global warming controversy]] by Christopher Essex and [[Ross McKitrick]].<ref name="Khandekar2005">{{cite journal|last=Khandekar|first=M. L.|first2=T. S. |last2=Murty |first3=P. |last3=Chittibabu|year=2005|title=The Global Warming Debate: A Review of the State of Science|journal=Pure and Applied Geophysics|volume=162|issue=8-9|pages=1557–1586|issn=0033-4553|doi=10.1007/s00024-005-2683-x|url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00024-005-2683-x}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Christopher Essex and Ross McKitrick, Taken by Storm: The Troubled Science, Policy and Politics of Global Warming (review)|journal=Australian Journal of Agricultural and Resource Economics|date=2004|volume=48|issue=2|pages=371–384|doi=10.1111/j.1467-8489.2004.00244.x|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1467-8489.2004.00244.x/abstract|accessdate=9 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lehrer|first1=Eli|title=Taken for a ride?(Science And Environment; Taken by Storm)(Brief Article)(Book Review)|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-109668548.html|accessdate=9 November 2015|publisher=The American Enterprise (subscription required)|date=October 1, 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Bocking|first1=Stephen|title=Reviewed Work: Taken by Storm: The Troubled Science, Policy and Politics of Global Warming by Christopher Essex, Ross McKitrick|journal=Canadian Public Policy|date=2004|volume=30|issue=3|pages=42–343|doi=10.2307/3552307|jstor=3552307}}</ref> The authors argue that politicians and others claim far more certainty than is justified by the science. The authors also argue that [[public policy]] discussions have abandoned science and resorted to ''[[ad hominem]]'' attacks.

''Taken by Storm'' was one of two runners up for the 2002 [[Donner Prize]] for the best book on Canadian public policy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Globalization book wins Donner Prize|url=https://global-factiva-com.ezproxy2.library.drexel.edu/ga/default.aspx|accessdate=9 November 2015|publisher=Calgary Herald (subscription required)|date=15 May 2003}}</ref>

